      <memberdef kind="define" id="group__iterable__section__apis_1gaf009fe4b90f7b338c3bf85bb4cd682e5" prot="public" static="no">
        <name>TYPE_SECTION_END_EXTERN</name>
        <param><defname>type</defname></param>
        <param><defname>secname</defname></param>
        <initializer>	extern type <ref refid="group__iterable__section__apis_1ga14d6bc375423775e5484183eeadd1fad" kindref="member">TYPE_SECTION_END</ref>(secname)[]</initializer>
        <briefdescription>
<para>iterable section extern for end symbol for a generic type </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Helper macro to give extern for end of iterable section. The macro typically will be called <ref refid="group__iterable__section__apis_1gaf009fe4b90f7b338c3bf85bb4cd682e5" kindref="member">TYPE_SECTION_END_EXTERN(struct foobar, foobar)</ref>. This allows the macro to hand different types as well as cases where the type and section name may differ.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
